reviewerName: J. Rose "JR From the Ball so Blue"
reviewText: OK.  It isn't Hamlet.  It is a movie about men who have sex with other men for money.  I saw this thing years ago, and there are moments of it that still stick.Like when one of the porn stars invites someone he really likes over and the camera crew catches him doing for love what he normally does for money and how upset he became.Then there's the famous Mr. Ward (Madonna's BoiToy) in the bathtub.This film will probably not convince many young men to enter this  business.  It might be best viewed the the fictional Skin and Bone as a 'things not to be when I grow up' film fest.
summary: Not Art -- Commerce.  But that's what we're selling...

reviewText: Another almost good film that got lost in itself. I was expecting more from this movie, but again just another "Hustler White" in sheeps clothing.
